# Local name denylist for bin/check-anonymization.sh — EXAMPLE.
#
# Copy this file to bin/anonymization-denylist.local (gitignored) and list
# the private / external project names and proprietary identifiers that must
# never appear verbatim in this public repo — one term per line. The scan
# greps every tracked file (case-insensitively) for each term.
#
# Why local-only: the .local file is gitignored, so the private names it lists
# are never themselves committed into this public repo. The .example you are
# reading is safe to commit because it contains no real names.
#
# Tip: prefer DISTINCTIVE terms. A project codename that is also a common
# English word will match unrelated prose and produce false positives; the
# scan can't tell the codename from the dictionary word.
#
# Format: one term per line; blank lines and #-comments ignored; inline
# "# comment" after a term is stripped.

# my-downstream-repo      # a project stamped from this template
# internal-daemon-name    # a private daemon/CLI not part of this template
